   Classroom Activities
   spacer
   Galileo K-12 Educator's Resources
   Educational materials for the Galileo Project.
   Goldstone-Apple Valley Radio Telescope (GAVRT) (Grades 5-12)
   Through the internet students connect to a 34-meter radio telescope to
   perform radio astronomy experiments.
   Lesson Plans (Grades 5-12)
   Earth and space science lessons.
   NSCAT (Grades 5-12)
   NASA Scatterometer for measuring sea winds, and JPL's Scatterometer
   Projects: NSCAT, QuikSCAT and SeaWinds.
   Practical Uses of Math And Science
   The On-line Journal of Math and Science Examples For Pre-College
   Education.
   Project SUN (Grades 8-12)
   Students Understanding Nature.
   Spaceborne Imaging Radar (Grades 5-14)
   Educational activities including lessons on radar, image processing,
   and scientific method.
   Stardust's "Think SMALL In A BIG Way" (Grades 5-8)
   This educator guide focuses on parts of the Solar System that do not
   get much attention; the small bodies of the Solar System, namely
   asteroids, meteoroids and comets.
   Telescopes in Education (Grades 3-14)
   Remote viewing opportunities using Mount Wilson Observatories' 24 inch
   telescope.

